#: ../source/reference/command/replSetMaintenance.txt:31
msgid ""
"Consider the following behavior when running the "
":dbcommand:`replSetMaintenance` command:"
msgstr ""

#: ../source/reference/command/replSetMaintenance.txt:34
msgid "You cannot run the command on the Primary."
msgstr ""

#: ../source/reference/command/replSetMaintenance.txt:36
msgid "You must run the command against the ``admin`` database."
msgstr ""

#: ../source/reference/command/replSetMaintenance.txt:38
msgid ""
"When enabled ``replSetMaintenance: true``, the member enters the "
"``RECOVERING`` state. While the secondary is ``RECOVERING``:"
msgstr ""

#: ../source/reference/command/replSetMaintenance.txt:41
msgid "The member is not accessible for read operations."
msgstr ""

#: ../source/reference/command/replSetMaintenance.txt:43
msgid "The member continues to sync its :term:`oplog` from the Primary."
msgstr ""

#: ../source/reference/command/replSetMaintenance.txt:45
msgid ""
"When a node receives a ``replSetMaintenance: true`` request, it adds a "
"maintenance mode task to a queue of tasks. If the queue of tasks was "
"empty and now is not, the node will transition to ``RECOVERING`` state "
"and begin to reject read requests. When a node receives a "
"``replSetMaintenance: false`` request, it removes a maintenance mode task"
" from the queue (even if that task was initiated by a different client). "
"If the request empties the maintenance mode task queue, the node will "
"return to ``SECONDARY`` state."
msgstr ""

#: ../source/reference/command/replSetMaintenance.txt:55
msgid ""
"If you want to prevent a node from servicing reads, consider using "
":doc:`/core/replica-set-hidden-member` instead."
msgstr ""

